Favour Ashe and Grace Nwokocha on Saturday won the 100m men and women race in Benin Edo State to become the new national champions. Ashe ran the second-fastest time of 9.99 seconds in the history of the national trials to upstage Enoch Adegoke, who due to injury could not defend his title. Deji Aliu in 2003 ran the fastest time of 9.99secs. Ashe, the Delta State athlete promised not to disappoint Nigerians at both the World Championships in Oregon and the Commonwealth Games in Birmingham. Alaba Akintola from Edo state placed second in 10.06 seconds, while Godson Oghenebrume placed third in 10.15seconds. In the women, Nwokocha representing Delta returned in 11.03 seconds to replace Blessing Okagbare as national champion. Rosemary Chukwuma also from Delta was second in 11.07seconds while Tina God bless was third in 11.38 secs. Tobi Amusan retained her national time with a time of 12.54secs. The championships will end today with the athletes for the world championships and the commyGames to be named.